flowRoot.flowPara: Ideas, observations, napkin drawings, good problem descriptions, solution suggestion blog posts, concept papers without a need for empirical data or proof-of-concept implementation

research (analysis + experimental implementations yielding empirical data), published papers. No need for formal specification of requirements, design or verification methods. Peer review at research level.
research elements turned into module implementations, either from scratch or based on existing prototypes
able to demonstrate limited functionality in a public or private test network (testnet)

develop a public fork/spin-off system based on an existing production system (which could be a previous spin-off) by producing a delta of system/subsystem requirements and associated design, implementation, tests and verification results
public test phase on test network of existing system, with clear test plan and quality gates to move to next phase: public test on main network.
Public test on main network with clear warning that this is a TEST ("Monopoly money"), and should not be treated as actual currency by anyone.
Active steps to minimize detrimental impacts on existing operational network (non-aggression principle). After final validation, production release, and move to operational maintenance.

text.tspan: A Proposal for how NASA's Technology Readiness Level (TRL) concept could be applied to guide a Bitcoin spin-off development lifecycle.
